      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE LUNCH (8) started hard in the market last start and was under pressure before the turn with a fading last over 2150m at Goulburn. Best figures measure up nicely and looks well placed with the claim on the firmer surface. FRICTIONAL FORCE (10) is progressing well as he gets up to his right distance range. Kept finding in the small field when second over 1900m at Casino in the heavy going. Maps well again and will prove hard to hold out. KISS'N DANCE (3) has only the one win from eighteen starts and failed on the quick back-up with a tiring fourth over 1900m at Casino two-and-a-half weeks ago. Sure to run well on the firmer surface. MONTEVECCHIO (6) finished second at Beaudesert two runs back but was less effective last time when sixth over 2180m at Ipswich. Gets one more chance with the 3kg claimer aboard. DIVINE EFFORT (2) returns from a let-up. Trained locally and stays in the calculations.",
